lk 中： </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a9c977121ceab416cfe8f3676&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Peak China with Noah Smith and Matt Klein&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Jordan Schneider&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/2qJWxeeMBnZA2QOxpIWsAa&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/2qJWxeeMBnZA2QOxpIWsAa" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>如果您愿意， <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/peak-china-with-noah-smith-and-matt-klein/id1289062927?i=1000628815608">可以在 Apple 播客上找到它</a>。我们讨论中国是否已经见顶，并讨论该国面临的经济挑战。马特和我基本上意见一致。中国正<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/china-at-the-peak">处于或接近相对巅峰</a>，但它仍然有能力创造惊人的成就，主导着全球制造业，而且不太可能很快衰落。</p><p>这是<a href="https://link.chtbl.com/Econ102">Erik Torenberg 主持的最新一集 Econ 102</a> ： </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a64b749255f97d9197cb3698f&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;E12: Why the Next Age of Globalization Will Be Awesome, a Cheaper US Dollar, and Reducing the Deficit&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/0dIHjczXdd3fXMHyaGCCz1&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/0dIHjczXdd3fXMHyaGCCz1" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>这里是<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/e12-why-the-next-age-of-globalization-will-be/id1696419056?i=1000629168698">Apple 播客</a>，这里是<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vNLkAqOtPYs">YouTube</a> 。我们谈论即将到来的全球化时代，工业化将蔓延到南亚和东南亚。我们还谈到了美国即将到来的财政紧缩压力时代</p><p>不管怎样，我们来看看本周的五件有趣的事情。</p><h4> 1.工薪阶层的财富正在改善</h4><p>许多美国人在 2010 年代学到的不言而喻的真理之一是，工人阶级的财富正在不断落后，但事实证明并非如此。人们“了解到”这个“事实”的可能原因是，<em>直到</em>2008年金融危机爆发时，人们才意识到这一点，并为此感到愤怒。</p><p>但无论如何，如果您从未见过美联储的<a href="https://www.federalreserve.gov/releases/z1/dataviz/dfa/distribute/chart/">分配金融账户</a>数据，您确实应该看一下。它允许您按百分位和各种人口统计数据绘制财富的组成部分（房地产、股票、消费者债务等）。令人沮丧的是，他们的图表工具似乎没有一个可以根据通货膨胀进行调整的选项，这一点很重要，因为通货膨胀决定了人们在给定的财富金额下可以购买多少<em>实物</em>。为此，我们必须访问<a href="https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/WFRBLB50107">FRED 网站</a>。但当我们这样做时，我们可以看到自 2012 年以来，底层 50% 的家庭的实际财富增长强劲： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44495a02-e15b-4e03-b2eb-fed90cbf1fff_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44495a02-e15b-4e03-b2eb-fed90cbf1fff_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44495a02-e15b-4e03-b2eb-fed90cbf1fff_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44495a02-e15b-4e03-b2eb-fed90cbf1fff_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44495a02-e15b-4e03-b2eb-fed90cbf1fff_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44